{
  "q1_accurate": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "consul.Server (file agent/consul/server.go, include_tests=false)", "note": "affected_via_composition gave me the full 31-holder direct-*Server set with file:line (ACL acl_endpoint.go:107, PeeringBackend peering_backend.go:31, raftHandle raft_handle.go:21, CertExpirationMonitor leader_metrics.go:114, stateLookup/queryServerWrapper prepared_query_endpoint.go:686/700) — section A of my answer is essentially this list, refined to exact field lines"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "consul.Server retained_via_interfaces", "note": "located the interface-typed holders I could not have named by grep: ACLResolver.backend acl.go:278, CAManager.delegate leader_connect_ca.go:60, ca.ConsulProvider.Delegate provider_consul.go:34, GatewayLocator.srv gateway_locator.go:44, rate.Handler.serversStatusProvider rate/handler.go:164, raft.Backend.handle storage/raft/backend.go:80, raft.forwardingClient.handle forwarding.go:115, v1compat.reconciler.config v1compat/controller.go:81, peerstream subscriptionManager/exportedServiceRequest, submatview LocalMaterializerDeps, local.State rpc state.go:172, agent.Agent delegate agent.go:234 — all cited in sections B/C/D/E"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "consul.Server affected_via_includes", "note": "the two embedded-*Server wrappers serverACLResolverBackend acl_server.go:110 and caDelegateWithState leader_connect_ca.go:90 — the hop that makes ACLResolver and CAManager server holders"},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "consul.Server (callers, depth 1)", "note": "pinned the type itself at agent/consul/server.go:169 and confirmed the composed_by set matched blast's, plus the acl.Server.requireLocalTokens edge at grpc-external/services/acl/server.go:68 that led me to the closure-field family in §C"}
  ],
  "q1_wrong": [
    {"tool": "sense_search", "query": "cluster server agent struct main server object", "note": "did not return consul.Server at all — top hits were testing/deployer/topology.Cluster, consul.Client, xds.clusterOpts. I identified the real target from sense_status's key_symbols ('consul.Server' appearing under acl.Config callers), not from this search"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "consul.Server retained_via_interfaces — carrier column", "note": "carrier attribution was wrong on most rows and produced 6 outright false positives I had to disprove: OverviewManager.stateProvider and usagemetrics stateProvider are s.fsm not the server (server.go:763,783); connectca.Config and serverdiscovery.Config Publisher are s.publisher (server_grpc.go:479,514); submatview LocalMaterializerDeps on the proxycfg-glue path is deps.EventPublisher. Carriers were also nonsensical on true rows — agent.Agent.delegate listed carrier 'serverACLResolverBackend' when the real value is *consul.Server itself (agent.go:709), same for GatewayLocator and rate.Handler"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "consul.Server", "note": "missed the largest holder family entirely: the 20 proxycfg-glue structs retaining ServerDataSourceDeps (glue.go:29), which carries ACLResolver: a.delegate and a GetStore closure over the server (agent.go:4658-4659). Not an interface, so retained_via_interfaces never saw it — I found it by reading agent.go around the proxycfg wiring"}
  ],
  "q2_fallbacks": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "consul.Server retained_via_interfaces", "fallback": "read", "missing": "the response explicitly says 'Which satisfier lands at runtime is unverified' — no construction site for any row, so every one of the 31 rows had to be checked against its actual wiring; I read agent/consul/server.go:520-800, server_grpc.go:330-545 and server_ce.go:190-220 to confirm or reject each"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "consul.Server (composition rows give struct ranges e.g. 107-110)", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "struct start line, not the retaining field line; I grepped for '*Server' field declarations to get acl_endpoint.go:108, peering_backend.go:33, leader_metrics.go:127 etc. so the audit points at the field a teammate must change"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "consul.Server", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "no coverage of function-valued struct fields — aclgrpc.Config's seven closures over s (grpc-external/services/acl/server.go:20-31) and the ForwardRPC/GetStore closures in six other gRPC configs are real retentions with no interface or type to follow; the index_caveat admits 'function-value passing (handlers stored as fields)' is missed but doesn't flag where"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "consul.Server", "fallback": "read", "missing": "no second-hop for handles passed onward — CAManager hands its caServerDelegate to ca.NewConsulProvider at leader_connect_ca.go:462 at leadership acquisition; blast listed ConsulProvider.Delegate as a holder but not how or when it gets there, which is the single most lifecycle-relevant fact in the audit"},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "consul.Server", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "peerstream's per-stream chain — I had subscriptionManager.backend and exportedServiceRequest.sub as fields but had to grep newSubscriptionManager/newExportedStandardServiceRequest and read stream_resources.go:345 and subscription_manager.go:750 to establish they carry PeeringBackend"}
  ],
  "q3_hints": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query_before": "sense_blast symbol=consul.Server (accepting retained_via_interfaces rows as given)", "query_after": "grep/sed over agent/consul/server.go, server_grpc.go, server_ce.go construction sites to verify each holder's actual value", "hint": "retained_note: 'Which satisfier lands at runtime is unverified' plus index_caveat 'Static graph may miss: method-on-field dispatch, function-value passing (handlers stored as fields)' — this directly caused the verification pass that caught all 6 false positives and, by making me read agent.go's wiring, the 20-holder proxycfg-glue family"},
    {"tool": "sense_search", "query_before": "sense_search 'cluster server agent struct main server object'", "query_after": "sense_blast/sense_graph symbol='consul.Server' file='agent/consul/server.go'", "hint": "not a hint but the miss itself — search returned topology.Cluster and consul.Client, so I dropped semantic search and went straight to symbol-addressed tools using the name I recovered from sense_status key_symbols"}
  ],
  "q4_value": "retained_via_interfaces — it named holders whose files never import agent/consul and never mention Server: rate.Handler.serversStatusProvider (rate/handler.go:164), internal/storage/raft Backend.handle and forwardingClient.handle, v1compat.reconciler.config, local.State's rpc field. With grep alone I would have had to guess every locally-declared interface name in the repo; this was exactly the easy-to-miss class the ticket was about, and it arrived in one call with file:line.",
  "q5_improve": "Attach the construction site to each retained_via_interfaces row instead of a guessed 'carrier'. The assignment expression is statically visible (server.go:633 '&serverACLResolverBackend{Server: s}', server_grpc.go:433 'FSMServer: s', server.go:783 'NewOverviewManager(s.logger, s.fsm, ...)') and would have both eliminated the 6 false positives and given me the leadership-time-vs-construction-time distinction I had to derive by hand. Second: extend the same retention pass to struct fields of func type that close over the symbol — that one gap hid the 20-holder proxycfg-glue family and seven aclgrpc closures, the highest-risk findings in the audit.",
  "score": 8,
  "score_rationale": "The composition and retained_via_interfaces output gave me holders like rate.Handler, internal/storage/raft, and v1compat.reconciler that no grep for 'Server' would have surfaced (Q1, Q4), but the unverified carriers produced 6 false positives and the closure-field blind spot hid the biggest family, so every row still needed a read of the wiring to finish (Q2, Q3) — faster with fallbacks, not fallback-free."
}

